<episodedetails><title>Le palais des réceptions et des congrès de Rome</title><plot>One of the most ambitious buildings of the Mussolini regime, the leader of Italy's modern movement attempted the impossible in combining fascism with modernity. It reflects Libera's great ability to design ambiguously in a spare, metaphysical language that sits on a knife-edge between modernism and neo-classicism.</plot></episodedetails>